column1: NF - kappaB represents a family of structurally related and evolutionarily conserved proteins ( p100 or NF - kappaB2, p105 or NF - kappaB1, p65 or RelA, RelB, c - Rel) that function as homodimers or heterodimers [ 1], and that regulate the expression of a large number of genes - such as TNF, IL - 1, IL - 6, cyclo - oxygenase - 2, chemokines, inducible nitric oxide synthase, and matrix metalloproteinases - that are involved in RA.
